                    "label": "We Value Your Feedback!",
                    "self": "http://blog.local/api/v1.0/blog/152",
                    "title": "We Value Your Feedback!",
                    "body": "<p>We’ve been getting a lot of suggestions for Drupalize.me video training topics lately. Boy, are you people demanding! Just kidding. :-) We <em>really appreciate</em> you letting us know about Drupal information you’re craving. <strong>We do read and consider your suggestions</strong> as we roadmap our future content. Some of those suggestions have already led to videos in the works right now. So thank you and keep 'em coming!</p>\n<h3>What's the best way to submit my ideas?</h3>\n<p><img class=\"screenshot\" src=\"http://drupalize.me/sites/drupalize.me/files/videola_blog_post_files/drupalizeme-feedback.jpg\" /></p>\n<p>If you've got ideas or requests for new videos or topics you'd love to see covered, we thought it might be helpful to know the best way to run 'em up the Drupalize.me flagpole. One of the best ways to do that is to go to click the \"Help &amp; Support\" link on Drupalize.me (it hangs out on the right hand side of the page all the time) and start a new discussion. You'll see a category there for \"Feedback and Accolades\" that you can use to create a new thread with your awesome idea. This lets us track all our user feedback and suggestions nicely and allows other users to +1 your suggestion if you make it a public discussion. It also will let you know, when you go to submit your discussion, if what you've typed in seems to closely match something another person has already posted (great minds think alike you know), saving you from duplicating a request and letting you just +1 another's. Bonus! Also, if you're just wanting to look around and see what others are suggesting you can always go to <a href=\"http://help.drupalize.me/discussions/suggestions\">http://help.drupalize.me/discussions/suggestions</a>. Be sure to +1 anything that gets you excited too.</p>\n<p>Our goal is to be your best resource for high-quality, relevant Drupal learning online, so keep the suggestions coming!</p>\n",
